Section 1:
Act 233 of the Regular Session
1 State of Arkansas As Engrossed: S1/27/25 S2/19/25
A Bill
2 95th General Assembly
3 Regular Session, 2025 SENATE BILL 94
4
5 By: Senator J. Dotson
6 By: Representative Achor
7
For An Act To Be Entitled
8
9 AN ACT CONCERNING THE REQUIREMENT FOR NEW ALL-TERRAIN
10 VEHICLE DEALERS AND NEW LOW SPEED VEHICLE DEALERS TO
11 MAINTAIN SERVICE AND PARTS STORAGE AREAS; AND FOR
12 OTHER PURPOSES.
13
14
Subtitle
15
16 TO AMEND THE REQUIREMENT FOR NEW ALL-
17 TERRAIN VEHICLE DEALERS AND NEW LOW
18 SPEED VEHICLE DEALERS TO MAINTAIN
19 SERVICE AND PARTS STORAGE AREAS.
20
21 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
22
23 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code ยง 23-112-302(e), concerning the requirements
24 for licensing of a new motor vehicle dealer, is amended to read as follows:
25 (e)(1) The Except as provided by subdivision (e)(2) of this section,
26 the applicant for a license as a new motor vehicle dealer shall furnish
27 satisfactory evidence that the applicant:
28 (1)(A) Maintains adequate space in the building or
29 structure wherein the applicant's established business is conducted for the
30 display of new motor vehicles or will have the facilities within a reasonable
31 time after receiving a license;
32 (2)(B) Has or will have adequate facilities in the
33 building or structure to perform repair and service work on motor vehicles
34 and adequate space for storage of new parts and accessories for the motor
35 vehicles; and
36 (3)(C) Will perform repair and warranty services on a
*ZRC008*
02-19-2025 14:51:46 ZRC008
As Engrossed: S1/27/25 S2/19/25 SB94
1 motor vehicle at the licensed location.
2 (2) A new all-terrain vehicle dealer or new low speed vehicle
3 dealer is not required to:
4 (A) Have a dedicated service and parts area inside of the
5 building or structure wherein the dealer's established business is conducted;
6 or
7 (B) Perform repair and warranty services on a motor
8 vehicle at the licensed location.
9 (3) A new all-terrain vehicle dealer or new low speed vehicle
10 dealer shall:
11 (A) Provide:
12 (i) Service of an all-terrain vehicle or low speed
13 vehicle sold by the new all-terrain vehicle dealer or new low speed vehicle
14 dealer; or
15 (ii) To the purchaser of the all-terrain vehicle or
16 low speed vehicle the name of a service provider within forty (40) miles of
17 the new all-terrain vehicle dealer or new low speed vehicle dealer that will
18 service the all-terrain vehicle or low speed vehicle sold by the new all-
19 terrain vehicle dealer or new low speed vehicle dealer to the purchaser;
20 (B) Provide a warranty or a manufacturer's warranty on an
21 all-terrain vehicle or low speed vehicle sold by the new all-terrain vehicle
22 dealer or new low speed vehicle dealer;
23 (C) Coordinate with a warranty service provider within
24 forty (40) miles of the new all-terrain vehicle dealer or new low speed
25 vehicle dealer to service the warranty or manufacturer's warranty provided
26 under subdivision (e)(3)(B) of this section;
27 (D) Submit the information concerning a service provider
28 or warranty service provider identified under subdivision (e)(3)(A)(ii) or
29 subdivision (e)(3)(C) of this section to the Arkansas Motor Vehicle
30 commission annually during the renewal of the license for the new all-terrain
31 vehicle dealer or new low speed vehicle dealer; and
32 (E) Provide information concerning a service provider or
33 warranty service provider identified under subdivision (e)(3)(A)(ii) or
34 subdivision (e)(3)(C) of this section to the purchaser of an all-terrain
35 vehicle or low speed vehicle sold by the new all-terrain vehicle dealer or
36 new low speed vehicle dealer.
2 02-19-2025 14:51:46 ZRC008
As Engrossed: S1/27/25 S2/19/25 SB94
1 (4) The Arkansas Motor Vehicle commission shall promulgate rules
2 to implement this section.
3
4 SECTION 2. DO NOT CODIFY. Application.
5 This act applies to all currently licensed new all-terrain vehicle
6 dealers and new low speed vehicle dealers and all applicants for a license as
7 a new all-terrain vehicle dealer or new low speed vehicle dealer.
8
9 /s/J. Dotson
10
